The paper deals with deep convolutional neural networks for image recognition tasks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) research. The paper also proposes a novel strategy for altering the architecture of a given CNN for a specified dataset, which involves optimizing accuracy and model size, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of empirical evaluation and experimentation, which suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
